      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scenarioCard">
      <h3>Best for Mixed Trays Under Limited Lights</h3>
      <p>
        A moderate cell count with slightly more room per plant is often the safest compromise because it protects peppers without overcrowding tomatoes too quickly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scenarioCard">
      <h3>Best for Gardeners Who Hate Potting Up</h3>
      <p>
        Start with more generous cells. Extra room up front is usually easier than reacting later when trays start running out of space.
      </p>
